HEADWORD: Stethometer
<hw>Ste*thom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ chest
+ <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>An apparatus for
measuring the external movements of a given point of the chest wall,
during respiration; -- also called
<altname>thoracometer</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

